news.title: NGT directs authorities to connect 93 villages of Greater Noida with sewage network
news.para: The green panel noted the villages have been provided with internal drains but these are yet to be connected to the main sewer line.

news.title: Supertech to give structural audit info of twin towers as sought by CBRI by Aug 7
news.para: CBRI's approval is required for Edifice to go ahead with the charging -- rigging of the twin towers with explosives -- at the site, a process which would need them around 15 days.

news.title: Lucknow development body to release Rs 18 crore to spruce up its 15 RWAs
news.para: The Resident Welfare Associations (RWA) of the respective buildings will use the fund for maintenance and repairing of buildings, including the lifts and generators.

news.title: Maharashtra: 126 more realtors to start flat registrations at own office
news.para: The move aims at reducing the footfall at the registration offices. An official of the state registration department said 72 developers were already making use of the facility in the state.

news.title: Online tenant checks in Maharashtra from August-end
news.para: Officials with the state registration department said while the process is currently underway in Pune and Mumbai, technical issues had kept it from a statewide rollout.

news.title: Bidhannagar: Salt Lake homes may be allowed extra floor
news.para: The Bidhannagar Municipal Corporation (BMC) has started working on a draft plan for this even as civic officials said the proposal has been discussed and accepted in an MMiC meeting.

news.title: Jharkhand: Gumla district administration fixes price to ease sand crisis
news.para: Gumla sub-divisional officer Ravi Anand met the sand traders, owners of stone crusher and brick kiln units on Thursday.

news.title: Bengaluru: Relief for Prestige Estates & Joy Ice Creams in land row
news.para: On October 6, 2017, while allowing their petitions, a single bench had quashed orders in relation to cancellation of grant of land made in favour of Joy Ice Creams by Karnataka Industrial Area Development Board (KIADB).

news.title: Chandigarh housing board set to auction 154 properties from August 16
news.para: Out of the 101 commercial properties, 99 will be auctioned on leasehold and the remaining on freehold basis. The reserve price and earnest amount will vary for property according to size, area and location.

news.title: Birla Corporation's net profit down 52% to Rs 62 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: However, its revenue from operation rose 26 per cent to Rs 2,203.76 crore during the quarter under review, as against Rs 1,749.11 crore in Q1 FY22.

news.title: Edifice Engineering submits debris management plan for Supertech twin towers
news.para: Authority officials said on Friday that they have received the report, which will be forwarded to the UP Pollution Control Board (UPPCB).

news.title: Nisus Finance invests over Rs 60 crore in EON Group's residential project in Mumbai
news.para: The project EON ONE spread over more than three-quarters of an acre near Siddhivinayak Temple involves redevelopment of an old housing society with rehabilitation of its existing 27 members.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: 100% land acquisition work for Jewar airport complete
news.para: UP's minister for industries and infrastructure development, Nand Gopal Gupta Nandi, confirmed that the land acquisition work is complete and the testing of the airport would begin in March 2024 while it would be ready for use by October 2024.

news.title: Oberoi Realty in talks to acquire 50-acre land in Gurugram
news.para: There is an under-construction residential tower on the property, developed by IREO Projects, with some sold units. Several homebuyers had approached the developer to help revive the project.

news.title: Indore civic body forms teams to collect construction waste
news.para: IMC commissioner Pratibha Pal directed all zonal officials to form separate teams and deploy vehicles to clear C&D waste in their respective areas timely.
